Wash and dry produce.

Zest and halve @Orange{1}; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Thoroughly
shake @Coconut Milk{1%unit} in container before opening.

> We sent more coconut milk!

== Chocolate Ganache ==

Place @coconut milk{1/4%cup} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until
bubbling, ~{40-60%seconds}. Immediately add half the @Semisweet Chocolate Chips{3%ounce}
and let stand until chocolate has slightly melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Gently whisk chocolate ganache until smooth and shiny, ~{30-60%seconds} more.
Wash and dry #whisk{}.

== Batter ==

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together @Crème Fraîche{2%tablespoon} and @water{1/4%cup}
until mostly smooth.

Add @Tempura Mix{82%g}, @Baking Powder{1/2%tablespoon}, @Brown Sugar{2%tablespoon},
remaining chocolate chips, @Orange Zest{1/4%tsp}, and @Salt{1/4%tsp} to bowl; whisk
until thoroughly combined, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Cooking ==

Coat two #microwave-safe mugs{2} with @Nonstick Cooking Spray{}. Evenly divide batter
between mugs.

> The batter will be sticky, so use a rubber spatula to transfer to mugs.

Microwave until mug muffins are springy to the touch and a #toothpick{} inserted
into the center comes out clean, ~{2%minutes}.

> If needed, continue to microwave in 30-second intervals until muffins are done.

Let mug muffins cool for ~{1%minute}. Serve straight from the mugs with orange
slices and ganache for dipping on the side.

> Not serving them right away? Use a butter knife to loosen muffins from mugs and
> transfer to a plate or container.